{"summary":"Patched /Users/roy/Downloads/data-plan.md and re-reviewed it. No findings rejected.","markdown_response":"Patched `/Users/roy/Downloads/data-plan.md` end to end and kept edits limited to that file.

Formal re-review result: no remaining plan-level contradictions found against the supplied review. I also addressed the delegated spot-review leftovers around bypass test wording, skipped ML-ready output metadata, derived-input freshness, GDELT default handling, official industry manifest reuse/discovery rules, benchmark import coverage, and deprecation sequencing.

Validation performed: re-read the full plan and searched for stale/conflicting terms including `--skip-gdelt-doc-api`, subprocess/deprecation sequencing, stale `20260424` usage, benchmark import coverage, and GDELT default behavior. No code tests were run because this was a markdown-only plan patch.","resolved_findings":["Sequenced deprecation after shared callable step APIs and production orchestrator migration, so direct CLI guards cannot break the canonical command.","Split ML-ready boundaries into `feature_snapshot_end`, `entry_data_end`, `label_complete_through`, `ml_training_label_end`, and `prediction_only_signal_end`; specified skipped metadata vs completed training artifacts.","Replaced the broad freshness gate with an endpoint and derived-input freshness registry, including requiredness by mode, lag, retry/backoff, blockers, optional stale handling, and consuming artifacts.","Changed GDELT DOC API handling from default-on/skip-flag to opt-in `--enable-gdelt-doc-api`, with missing/stale DOC diagnostics recorded as optional skipped status by default.","Changed official industry manifest behavior so daily/monthly defaults validate and reuse a pinned manifest, with discovery/build only when coverage/staleness requires it or full-refresh requests it.","Added a central per-CLI bypass helper contract requiring explicit real arguments for production-sensitive defaults and output paths.","Added `quant-import-benchmark-constituents` to the manual-step policy and tests, with explicit handling if documented as an official import.","Tightened deprecation tests so bypass preserves standalone behavior only after required explicit arguments are confirmed.","Added tests for derived-input freshness, skipped ML-ready outputs, default GDELT opt-in behavior, and sequencing of deprecation guards after internal API migration."],"rejected_findings":[],"touched_files":["/Users/roy/Downloads/data-plan.md"],"unresolved_questions":[]}
